assumes h0 : "\<forall> x. x < -3 \<longrightarrow> f x = 3 * x + 5"
and h1 : "\<forall> x. x \<ge> -3 \<longrightarrow> f x = 7 - 4 * x"
shows  "f 5 = -13"
a_0.formal solution:

\begin{cases}
3x + 5 &\text{if }x<-3, \\
7-4x&\text{if }x\ge -3.

 ### Proof
 Because $5\ge -3$, we use the second case to determine that $f(5) = 7-4(5) = \boxed{-13}$.
 *)
